@NODE Intro "AttachMail - Introduction"
@{fg shine}Introduction@{fg text}
@{par}AttachMail is a function to attach files from Opus5 (v5.5+) into a YAM (v1.3.4+) message. YAM doesn't feature an appicon or an appwindow on which you can drag and drop icons to attach one or more files while you write an email.
@{par}As this feature is not a priority for the YAM author, and Opus5 is fully scriptable (yep, and it's even easier to script than the MacOS Finder), I have decided to write this small function. Select 150 files and send these with a click of the mouse...
@{par}AttachMail uses Opus' File Types to find the proper MIME type of each item to attach.
@{par} File Type ID     MIME type
 JPEG             image/jpeg
 GIF              image/gif
 HTML             text/plain
 MPEG             video/mpeg
 8SVX             audio/basic
 Others           application/octet-stream
@{par}This script is versatile as it can be used as a button, menu, or anything else...
@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "AttachMail - Installation"
@{fg shine}Installation@{fg text}
@{par}First, copy AttachMail.dopus in DOpus5:ARexx drawer.
@{par}Now, you must be familiar with Opus5 configuration tools. If you're not, please read the manual again.
@{par}AttachMail is usable as an external function so his action is defined via the Function Editor.
@{par}  1. Create a new object (button, menu, appicon,... ) and go in the Function Editor.
@{par}  2. Select ARexx as the function type.
@{par}  3. Choose @{b}DOpus5:ARexx/AttachMail.dopus5@{ub} with the folder icon.
@{par}  4. Add @{b}{Qp}@{ub} and @{b}{Ql}@{ub} as parameters.
@{par}  5. And press Return.
@{par}  6. Now, you see 'ARexx DOpus5:Arexx/AttachMail.dopus5 {Qp} {Ql}' in the main list.
@{par}  7. Click on 'Use' button.
@{par}  8. And click on 'Save' to keep your changes.
@{par}  9. The function can now be @{"used" LINK Usage}.
@{par}@{fg shine}Notes@{fg text}
@{par}- {Qp} is used to send the current DOpus ARexx port to the function.
@{par}- {Ql} to pass the handler of source window.
@{par}- you can add a third parameter to specify the encoding type. Values are 'UU' to uuencode file or 'MIME' to use the MIME method to attach file. MIME is the default value.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "AttachMail - Usage"
@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

See @{" Installation " LINK Installation} before you read this chapter.

@{fg shine}YAM limitations@{fg text}

YAM has a basic ARexx interface, and it limits the way you work with the AttachMail function.

a. Before attaching, you must first start to write a mail (click on the 'Write' button), otherwise, the files are never attached.

b. The YAM interface can't be locked so verify if all files are attached before sending the mail.

@{fg shine}What can you attach?@{fg text}

AttachMail works only on the selected source list, and you can only attach files, not drawers. If you attach a drawer, nothing will happen.

@{fg shine}How to stop attachment?@{fg text}

Click on the 'Abort' button if you want to stop the attachment.
@ENDNODE
